                                                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                                                    <div class="col-12">
                                                                        <h2 class="tm-page-title">What is verbal abuse?</h2>
                                                                    </div>
                                                                </div>
                                                                <div class="row">
                                                                    <p>Verbal abuse is a key feature of emotionally abusive relationships. The perpetrator consistently makes statements that negatively label a person. This has a serious impact on the self-esteem and confidence of the person experiencing the verbal abuse.</p>
                                                                    <p>
                                                                        Typical Signs are:<br>
                                                                        - swearing and continual humiliation, in private or in public <br>
                                                                        - attacks on intelligence, sexuality, body image and capacity as a parent and spouse<br>
                                                                        - ridiculing religious beliefs or ethnic background<br>
                                                                        - screaming, shouting, name-calling, put-downs<br>
                                                                    </p>

